We harnessed the Swin UNETR (Extended Data Fig. 6)74,75, a three-dimensional (3D) transformer-based architecture, to extract embeddings from a multitude of brain MRI scans, encompassing various sequences including T1w, T2w, SWI and FLAIR imaging sequences. The Swin UNETR model consists of a Swin Transformer encoder, designed to operate on 3D patches, seamlessly connected to a convolutional neural network-based decoder through multi-resolution skip connections. Commencing with an input volume \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
